  • All Implemented Interfaces:

    Direct Known Subclasses:
    TypeFactImpl

    public class FactImpl
extends AssertionImpl
implements com.cyc.kb.Fact
    A fact object is an assertion with a variable-free sentence with no conjunctions or operators (a ground atomic formula), and a facade for #$CycLGAFAssertion. In general, this class is used to create and remove arbitrary assertions from Cyc.

    1.0

      • isValidCore

        protected boolean isValidCore(CycObject cycObject)
        This not part of the public, supported KB API. Check that the candidate core object is valid Ground Automic Formula. In the CycKB the object would be valid #$CycLGAFAssertion Internally this method checks if the the cycObject is an instance of CycAssertion and it is fully grounded, i.e. has not open variables.
        Overrides:
        isValidCore in class AssertionImpl
        Parameters:

      • replaceTerms

        protected <O> O replaceTerms(Map substitutions)
                      throws com.cyc.kb.exception.KbTypeException,
                             com.cyc.kb.exception.CreateException
        Replace non-destructively a set of objects with another set of objects, in a Non-Atomic Term or a Sentence. Replacement is not supported within Assertions, Atomic Terms, Variables and Symbols. Although, set of objects replaced can be any KBObject or Java primitive object.
        Type Parameters:
        O -
        Parameters:
        substitutions - the replacement mapping
        Returns:
        A new object with the substitutions made in the original object
        Throws:
        com.cyc.kb.exception.KbTypeException
        com.cyc.kb.exception.CreateException
